<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-417] modify Manual 37.4.2.1, Tuning File Read Ahead, to include description of &#8220;max_read_ahead_per_file_mb&#8221; </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-417</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre Manual section 37.4.2.1, Tuning File Read Ahead, describes both &#8220;max_read_ahead_mb&#8221; and &#8220;max_read_ahead_whole_mb&#8221; but there is no mention of &#8220;max_read_ahead_per_file_mb.&#8221;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be useful first to add a description of the effects of setting max_read_ahead_per_file_mb and then also to include its interactions with the other already-mentioned parameters.&#160; For example, it seems that the order of setting these parameters makes a difference in whether the values are accepted or rejected as &quot;out of range.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
